The paper proposes a new approach for approximate evaluation of #P-hard queries with probabilistic databases, which is a topic related to databases and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses relational query optimization techniques, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
